\int \frac{1}{1-\sqrt[]x} dx 
1-\sqrt[]x=u
du= -\frac{1}{2 \sqrt[]x}dx \rightarrow 2(u-1)du=dx 
2 \int \frac{u-1}{u}du = 2\int du - 2 \int \frac{1}{u}du= 2u - 2 \ln(u) = 2(1-\sqrt[]x)-2(\ln(1-\sqrt[]x)) 
2 \int \frac{u-1}{u}du \quad = \quad 2\int du - 2 \int \frac{1}{u}du 
 = \quad 2u - 2 \ln(|u|) + c 
 = 2(1-\sqrt[]x)-2(\ln(1-\sqrt[]x)) + c
= 2 - 2\sqrt x - 2\ln|1 - \sqrt x| + c 
 = -2\sqrt x - 2 \ln|1 - \sqrt x| + C
c
2 + c = C
c
C
\ln
\int \frac 1u du = \ln|u| + C
\ln|1 - \sqrt x|
\ln|\sqrt x - 1|
|1 - \sqrt x| = |\sqrt x - 1|,\quad \text{just as}\quad |1 - 3| = |3 - 1| = 2
